# MCP Tools Reference for 1C Development

This file describes available MCP tools for 1C development. Reference this file instead of duplicating tool descriptions.

## Code & Documentation Search

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **docsearch** | Search 1C platform documentation | Verify built-in function existence, check method signatures, find platform features |
| **codesearch** | Search existing configuration code | Find patterns, check usages, verify implementations exist |
| **templatesearch** | Search code templates and examples | Find architectural patterns, get implementation examples before writing code |
| **helpsearch** | Search 1C help by function description | Find metadata objects by their purpose |
| **ssl_search** | Search SSL (БСП) functions | Find standard library functions to reuse |

## Metadata Tools

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **search_metadata** | Search configuration metadata structure | Verify object existence, check attributes, find relationships (preferred) |
| **metadatasearch** | Same as search_metadata | Alternative name for same functionality |
| **get_metadata_prompt** | Get instructions for cypher query | When search_metadata unavailable |
| **execute_metadata_cypher** | Execute metadata cypher query | After get_metadata_prompt |
| **business_search** | Semantic search for metadata | Find objects by natural language description |
| **answer_metadata_question** | Get answers about metadata objects | Understand how metadata objects work |

## Code Quality Tools

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **syntaxcheck** | Check BSL syntax and style | After writing code, verify no errors. **Limit: 3 times per cycle** |
| **check_1c_code** | Analyze for logic and performance issues | Find performance problems, logic errors |

## Tool Usage by Task

### Writing New Code
1. **templatesearch** — find similar implementations
2. **codesearch** — check existing patterns
3. **search_metadata** — verify metadata structure
4. **docsearch** — verify built-in functions
5. **ssl_search** — find reusable SSL functions
6. **syntaxcheck** — verify syntax after writing

### Code Review
1. **codesearch** — verify pattern compliance
2. **search_metadata** — check correct metadata usage
3. **docsearch** — verify method/property existence
4. **check_1c_code** — find issues

### Architecture Design
1. **search_metadata** — understand existing structure
2. **codesearch** — find existing patterns
3. **templatesearch** — find architectural templates

### Documentation
1. **codesearch** — find code to document
2. **search_metadata** — understand metadata structure
3. **helpsearch** — reference platform documentation

### Error Fixing
1. **syntaxcheck** — identify syntax errors
2. **docsearch** — verify correct function names
3. **search_metadata** — verify metadata object names
4. **codesearch** — find correct usage patterns

### Performance Optimization
1. **codesearch** — find slow patterns
2. **search_metadata** — check indexes
3. **check_1c_code** — analyze performance issues
4. **templatesearch** — find optimized patterns

## Important Rules

1. **Always search before writing** — use templatesearch and codesearch first
2. **Verify against documentation** — use docsearch for built-in functions
3. **Check metadata exists** — use search_metadata before using objects
4. **Limit syntaxcheck** — maximum 3 times per cycle, then move on
5. **Prefer search_metadata** — over metadatasearch when both available
6. **Don't use Grep** — when MCP tools are available for code search
